# Korrath, the Abyssal Commander — Hero Design Document

**Version:** 0.1 (pre-alpha)
**Faction:** Abyss Order
**Status:** Design phase

-----

## 1. Hero Identity

**Name:** Korrath, the Abyssal Commander
**Faction:** Abyss Order
**Resource System:** Standard Essence / Mana

Korrath is a dark knight commander who channels abyssal energy through physical dominance, corruption stripping, and runic power. Unlike Vael’s imp swarm or Seris’s flesh economy, Korrath is built around a singular powerful frontline unit that transforms through branch investment — a patient, escalating threat that grows more dangerous the longer it survives.

-----

## 2. New Mechanics

### Armour

A defensive stat that reduces incoming physical attack damage by its value.

|Rule             |Detail                                                               |
|-----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Damage reduction |Reduces physical attack damage by Armour value                       |
|Minimum damage   |Physical attacks always deal at least 100 damage regardless of Armour|
|Spell interaction|Spells bypass Armour entirely — full damage always lands             |
|Stacking         |Armour stacks permanently unless removed                             |

### Armour Break

A stackable debuff applied to enemy minions and heroes.

|Rule                      |Detail                                                                                |
|--------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|Primary function          |Reduces target’s Armour by its value first                                            |
|Secondary function        |If Armour Break exceeds target’s Armour, excess converts to flat bonus physical damage|
|Against unarmoured targets|Functions purely as flat bonus physical damage                                        |
|Stacking                  |Permanent, stacks indefinitely                                                        |

**Resolution order for physical attacks against armoured targets:**

1. Armour Break reduces target Armour first
1. Remaining Armour reduces incoming damage
1. If Armour Break exceeds Armour value, excess adds flat bonus damage
1. Minimum 100 damage always applies

### Formation (Keyword)

When this minion is placed adjacent to another minion of the same race, trigger this effect once permanently. Order does not matter — the effect triggers regardless of which minion is placed first.

- One-time trigger per minion pair
- Does not retrigger if adjacency is broken and reformed
- Each new adjacent same-race minion is a fresh Formation trigger

