## 5. Talent Tree

Korrath has 3 talent branches, each with 4 tiers. One talent point is granted at run start and one per act boss defeat (up to 4 total).

-----

### Branch 1 — Infernal Bulwark

*Focus: Human formation, Armour stacking, patient investment, Guard capstone*

The knight becomes a Human anchor for a disciplined formation. Armour accumulates through Formation triggers and converts directly into ATK. The capstone makes the knight an immovable guardian that doubles all future Armour gains.

|Tier|ID              |Name             |Effect                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
|----|----------------|-----------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|T0  |iron_formation  |Iron Formation   |Abyssal Knight’s race becomes Human. Abyssal Knight gains the Formation keyword: the first time a Human is placed adjacent to the knight, it permanently gains 200 Armour and 200 HP (triggers once only)|
|T1  |commanders_reach|Commander’s Reach|Aura: while Abyssal Knight is on board, adjacent friendly Humans apply 100 Armour Break to their attack target on each attack                                                                            |
|T2  |iron_resolve    |Iron Resolve     |All friendly Humans gain ATK equal to their current Armour value (passive, always active)                                                                                                                |
|T3  |unbreakable     |Unbreakable      |CAPSTONE: Abyssal Knight gains Guard. All Armour gains on Abyssal Knight are doubled                                                                                                                     |

**Branch notes:**

- T0 Formation is a one-time permanent trigger — does not retrigger on subsequent adjacent humans
- T2 conversion is a live passive — as Armour changes, ATK updates accordingly
- T3 Guard forces all enemy attacks into the knight; doubled Armour gains amplify T2’s ATK conversion simultaneously
- Branch wants a human-heavy deck from run start

-----

### Branch 2 — Runic Knight

*Focus: Double race tag, rune generation through attacks, rune aura absorption, Grand Ritual Chaos capstone*

The knight transcends its origin through runic empowerment, gaining both Human and Demon tags. Every attack generates a random rune. Overflow runes are absorbed as permanent auras. The capstone fires Grand Ritual Chaos — three volatile effects with one randomly enhanced post-resolution.

|Tier|ID                 |Name               |Effect                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
|----|-------------------|-------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|T0  |runic_transcendence|Runic Transcendence|Abyssal Knight gains both Human and Demon race tags simultaneously. Whenever Abyssal Knight attacks, place a random Rune on your board                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
|T1  |runic_absorption   |Runic Absorption   |When your rune board is full (3 active runes) and Abyssal Knight generates a new rune, randomly destroy one active rune and permanently grant its aura to a random Abyssal Knight on board. Stacks — the same aura type can be granted multiple times                                                                                                |
|T2  |runic_empowerment  |Runic Empowerment  |Choose one permanently: **Path of Demons** — when a Demon is summoned, deal 50 damage × total active rune auras (rune slots + knight aura stacks) to a random enemy, repeated that many times. **Path of Humans** — when a Human is summoned, give 50 ATK × total active rune auras to a random friendly minion, repeated that many times            |
|T3  |grand_ritual_chaos |Grand Ritual: Chaos|CAPSTONE: Consume any 3 active runes → trigger 3 volatile effects simultaneously. Each effect has inherent damage/value variance (rolls within a range). After all effects resolve, randomly reveal one as Enhanced — its output is massively amplified. T1 triggers three times simultaneously, granting three rune auras to a random Abyssal Knight|

**Rune aura count for T2 (X):**
X = active rune slots on board + total aura stacks absorbed by all Abyssal Knights via T1

**T1 interaction with T3:**
Consuming 3 runes via Chaos triggers T1 three times — the knight absorbs three aura stacks in the same turn Chaos resolves. X increases by 3 after Chaos fires.

**Branch notes:**

- Random rune generation introduces variance the player adapts to rather than controls
- T2 path choice commits the deck to Demon flood or Human summon identity
- T3 Enhanced reveal happens after all effects resolve — the chaos is embraced, not gamed
- Branch is dependent on the knight attacking consistently; removal stalls rune generation
- Both demon and human paths remain functional without the knight via T2 summon triggers

